      "```\r\nr.table(\"user\").get(1).merge(r.table(account).get(r.row(\"accountId\")))\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf the user exists but not the account, I would expect to get the user, not `null`.\r\n\r\n\r\n`x.merge(null)` should whether throw an error (like `x.merge(\"string\")` or return `x` I think.\r\nIf we throw an error, people can avoid it by adding a `default` somewhere.\r\n\r\n\r\n"
